-# Platform Architecture
+## What is StitchCore
 
-The StitchCore ecosystem is organized into three layers.
+StitchCore is the company and technology platform behind Sidekick Air and all future rigid inflatable human-support products.
 
-StitchCore (Company and Platform)
+StitchCore does not describe a single product. It describes a structural engineering approach, a design philosophy, and a long-term product family architecture.
 
-AeroStitch Core Technology (Structural Technology)
+The name reflects the core technology: drop-stitch construction, where thousands of internal threads (stitches) are bonded between two parallel coated fabric surfaces, creating a rigid structural panel when pressurized.
 
-Sidekick Air (Product)
-
-This structure separates the company, the underlying engineering system, and the individual commercial products.
-
