-# AeroStitch Core Technology
+## Why a Platform Architecture
 
-AeroStitch Core Technology is the structural engineering system developed by StitchCore.
+Building around a platform rather than a single product creates several strategic advantages.
 
-This technology uses high-pressure drop-stitch textile construction to create rigid inflatable platforms capable of supporting significant loads while remaining lightweight and portable.
+Engineering leverage
+Core structural knowledge developed for Sidekick Air applies directly to future products. The same materials, seam techniques, valve systems, and pressure specifications can be reused across the product family.
 
-Key characteristics include:
+IP leverage
+Provisional patents filed for the core technology protect not just the first product but the entire class of rigid inflatable human-support platforms. This creates a defensive moat around the category.
 
-woven drop-stitch internal structural matrix  
-TPU-coated textile layers  
-high-pressure structural inflation  
-rigid load-bearing performance  
-modular attachment interface integration  
+Manufacturing leverage
+Manufacturing relationships built for Sidekick Air can scale to support the full product family without starting over.
 
-AeroStitch Core Technology enables inflatable structures to function as rigid support platforms suitable for clinical and structural applications.
+Market leverage
+Each product within the platform reinforces the others. A therapist who uses Sidekick Air understands the StitchCore value proposition when a Sidekick Sport product enters their environment.
 
-This technology forms the engineering foundation for all StitchCore products.
-
